# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp has a system of specialized chat template handlers in `common/chat.cpp` that bypass the generic Jinja template renderer for models with well-known, stable prompt formats. The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format (`[INST]`/`[/INST]` wrapping without `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`) is used by Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 and compatible models. Adding a dedicated handler ensures correct prompt construction for this format.

---

## Critical Files

- **`common/chat.cpp`** — all changes happen here (two insertion points)
- **`common/chat.h`** — read-only; provides `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` (already exists)

---

## Step 1 — Add the Handler Function

**Insertion point:** After `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3` ends at **line 1517**, before `namespace workaround {` at line 1519.

Add the following function:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string pending_system;
    data.prompt = tmpl.bos_token();

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        const auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            pending_system = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            std::string effective = content;
            if (!pending_system.empty()) {
                effective = pending_system + "\n" + effective;
                pending_system.clear();
            }
            data.prompt += "[INST] " + effective + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

**Key design points:**
- Uses `tmpl.bos_token()` for the leading `<s>` (model-agnostic).
- System message is held in `pending_system` and prepended with `\n` to the next user message.
- User turns: `[INST] {content} [/INST]`
- Assistant turns: ` {content}</s>` (note leading space — matches Mistral v0.3 spec).
- No PEG parser, grammar, or preserved tokens — this is `CONTENT_ONLY`.

---

## Step 2 — Register Detection in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`

**Insertion point:** Inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (starts at **line 1634**), add a new `if` block just before `return std::nullopt;` at **line 1690**.

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] wrapping without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    // Distinguish from Ministral 3 handler which requires [SYSTEM_PROMPT] presence
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

**Why placed last:** The `[INST]`/`[/INST]` markers are common (e.g. also appear in Llama-2 templates). Placing this check last ensures all more-specific handlers (Ministral 3, GPT-OSS, Functionary, Kimi K2, LFM2, LFM2.5, GigaChatV3) match first.

---

## Expected Prompt Output

| Input | Output |
|---|---|
| `[system="S", user="U1", assistant="A1", user="U2"]` | `<s>[INST] S\nU1 [/INST] A1</s>[INST] U2 [/INST]` |
| `[user="U1", assistant="A1", user="U2"]` | `<s>[INST] U1 [/INST] A1</s>[INST] U2 [/INST]` |
| `[user="U1"]` | `<s>[INST] U1 [/INST]` |

---

## Verification

1. **Build check:** `cmake --build build -j` — confirm no compilation errors in `common/chat.cpp`.
2. **Unit test:** If `tests/test-chat-template.cpp` exists, add a test case for the `mistral-instruct-v3` detection and prompt output.
3. **Manual test:** Run `llama-cli` or `llama-server` with a Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 GGUF model and inspect the rendered prompt — it should match the format above.
4. **Non-regression:** Ensure the Ministral 3 handler still triggers correctly for templates containing `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]` + `[ARGS]`.

